`crates/steno` is the Rust workspace member implementing the `.steno` → Plover dictionary / LSP snippet compiler. It contains two subtrees: `src/`, the library and its `bin/` binaries (the actual pipeline: parse → expand → render/blocks/snippet, plus stroke handling, editor keystroke IR, and JSON serialization), and `tests/`, the integration suite that exercises that pipeline end-to-end through its public functions.

The coupling between the two subtrees is one-directional and narrow: `tests/` depends only on `src/`'s re-exported public surface (`parse_source`, `parse_template`, `expand_counts`, `expand_types_one`, `render_plain`, `render_smart`, `emit_struct`, `build_plain_dict`, `build_smart_dict`) — it never reaches into submodule internals. Because of this, `tests/` acts as the executable spec for `src/`'s stage contracts: any change to `Chunk`/`Expr`/`TypedEntry`/`EntryFlags` shapes, to `PLAIN`/`SMART`/`SMART_INDENT` behavior presets, or to error-message wording in `error.rs`, must be cross-checked against `tests/` (specifically `editor.rs`, `parse_template.rs`, `parse_source.rs`, and the two hand-built `TypedEntry` constructions in `smart.rs`/`snippet.rs`) since those tests pin exact literals rather than semantic behavior.

A second cross-cutting fact spanning both subtrees: most of `tests/` reads the real `dict.steno` corpus at the repo root rather than fixtures, so that corpus is effectively part of this crate's test contract — editing dictionary entries for specific hardcoded strokes, or shrinking/growing the corpus past the >1000-entry floor several tests assert, breaks `tests/` independently of any `src/` code change.

No `intent.md` is present for this directory, so no divergence can be assessed.